name: Shelley
description:
Necklace

This necklace is truly one-of-a-kind with large shimmering full Abalone Shells in whispering hues of cream, pink and Aegan green; Genuine Freshwater Pearls and Rhodium Plated Silver chain, accents and clasp.
Each Abalone Shell is linked by hand-worked-wire for a distinctive rustic look. Careful attention to detail was required to complete this original by DD and there is no other available (we do not duplicate our jewelry designs).

Abalone Shells (30mm or 1 1/8" long)

Neck sz: 18" + 3" extension


NOTE: This necklace is crafted from Pearls and Abalone Shells, therefore it is recommended to avoid contact with chemicals, creams, perfumes or soap - these will affect the natural finish.
To avoid wear and tarnishing, store in an Anti-tarnish box / bag.

name: Strung Icicles
description:
This monochromatic bracelet resembles the frosted icicles that form in the winter, with beautiful Firepolished Czech glass beads, Handmade Lampwork glass beads, Textured Glass Pearls, Pressed glass and numerous glass spacers strung with Silver Plated Daisy beads, clasp and accents. 
A bold, elegant piece that completes any ensemble and must be stored in order to avoid tarnishing.

Wrist sz: 8 1/4" approximate closure (toggle clasp)

name: Caribbeana
description:
This wide, colorful and prominent necklace is completely hand-worked with silver wire, crocheted with hundreds of beautiful Turquoise glass beads and finished with Tibetan Silver cones. Time intensive, the entire process requires five hours of detailed workmanship and the end result is one-of-a-kind beautiful.
Reg. $79.99

Neck sz: 18" + 3" extension
